Following the drama rocking the primaries and Osun election in Nigeria, Aisha Jummai Al-Hassan, popularly known as Mama Taraba has resigned from her position as the Minister of Women Affairs under the President Muhammadu Buhari cabinet. This is coming after she was disqualified from the APC Taraba governorship primaries. According to her letter, “no reason was given for her disqualification” yet Nigerians claim that her disqualification is linked to her open support for former vice president and president hopeful Atiku Abubakar. Since the letter was made public, Nigerians have been reacting to the news. See some of them below:      